`gon.onChange` pushes a callback into a plain array but has no unsubscribe mechanism (it returns `undefined`). The `useEffect` hook here has an empty dependency array and no cleanup, so every time `SessionList` mounts, a new `setVaultStatus` reference is pushed onto `listeners["vault_status"]`. If the component is unmounted and remounted (e.g., via SPA navigation or parent re-renders), the stale `setVaultStatus` closures pile up — each queuing a state update on the old (dead) component instance.

Consider adding an `offChange` / `removeListener` export to `gon.js` and returning a cleanup function:

```js
useEffect(() => {
    setVaultStatus(gon.get("vault_status"));
    gon.onChange("vault_status", setVaultStatus);
    return () => gon.offChange("vault_status", setVaultStatus);
}, []);
```

