When a session expires, all in-flight RPC calls are likely to return `UNAUTHORIZED` at nearly the same time. Each one dispatches `moltis:auth-status-changed`, which in turn fires a `fetch("/api/auth/status")` from the event listener in `app.js`. This means N concurrent fetches and potentially N concurrent `window.location.assign("/login")` calls — which is harmless in practice but wasteful.

Consider debouncing the dispatch, or tracking a "redirect in progress" flag to skip redundant dispatches:

```js
